e explained that “on receipt of information of a suspected outbreak, the Ministry dispatched a medical team led by the Director of Public Health, Dr. Terna Kur and an Incident Manager, Emergency Operation Centre, Dr. Terungwa Ngishie who went in and confirmed the outbreak after diagnosis.” The Commissioner stated that Governor Samuel Ortom through the Ministry had released N3.1million for an emergency response to the outbreak at Obagaji and Abinsi. He said the Ministry was working round the clock to contain the outbreak and advised the people to maintain personal hygiene, get their drinking water from clean sources as well as purify their water before drinking to check the further outbreak of the disease in the state. Vanguard News Nigeria Two persons were feared dead in a fresh outbreak of cholera at Otukpo town, in Otukpo Local Government Area of Benue State. November 7, 2013 In "News" The death toll in the recent cholera outbreak in Otukpo Local Government Area of Benue State has continued to rise with the epidemic claiming 12 more lives, including women and children. November 15, 2013 In "News" These fresh outbreaks have created panic among Nigerians particularly residents of affected areas. What does this development mean for Nigeria? Are there lessons to be learned? September 9, 2018 In "Health"